urce/Manila\", \"score\": 0.9990278231314632, \"rank\": 0.0009730369686984609, \"text\": \"Manila\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Manila\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was exactly how Marcial and his team had pictured the fight ending, with the Filipino stopping Joseph at the 1:55 mark of the third round of their eight-round middleweight duel to hike his professional record to 6-0 (4 KOs).\", \"from\": 659, \"to\": 886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 757, \"end\": 763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"score\": 0.9993625596794964, \"rank\": 0.00035304617474101884, \"text\": \"Joseph\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was our plan - to adjust and [establish] good defense in the first two rounds, get the timing, then go for the knockout in the third and fourth.\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 1038, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Our plan was successful,\\\" said Marcial in Filipino.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1090, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Marcial fought for the first time since the Paris Games in July 2024, when he lost hisopening boutto Uzbekistan's Turabek Khabibullaev as he missed out on an Olympic medal repeat after bagging bronze in the Tokyo Games in 2021.\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1319, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1193, \"end\": 1203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9659809084862864, \"rank\": 0.03413129973989228, \"text\": \"Uzbekistan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Uzbekistan_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was also his first professional bout in over a year since he knocked out Thailand's Thoedsak Sinam at home at the Ninoy Aquino Stadium in March 2024.\", \"from\": 1321, \"to\": 1473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1397, \"end\": 1405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thailand\", \"score\": 0.6193461038808387, \"rank\": 0.6140145751132564, \"text\": \"Thailand\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thailand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thailand\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the Zamboangue\\u00f1o banked on his power to make quick work of Joseph, a replacement for original opponent Alexis Gaytan, for his third consecutive stoppage victory.\", \"from\": 1475, \"to\": 1640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1483, \"end\": 1495, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chavacano\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.133145327610418e-18, \"text\": \"Zamboangue\\u00f1o\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chavacano\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chavacano\"}, {\"begin\": 1538, \"end\": 1544, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"score\": 0.9993625596794964, \"rank\": 0.00035304617474101884, \"text\": \"Joseph\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Joseph\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was getting used to the feeling of being in the ring.\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1698, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But because of my experience, we got the win,\\\" said Marcial.\", \"from\": 1699, \"to\": 1759, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Marcial said he will remain in the United States to train for a potential boxing event later this year in celebration for the 50th anniversary of the iconic Thrilla in Manila, where the legendary Muhammad Ali edged Joe Frazier at the Araneta Coliseum in 1975.\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 2020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1796, \"end\": 1809, \"title\": \